Reasoning: The paper focuses on deep learning models and their applications in real-world scenarios, specifically in image recognition. This aligns with the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the inspiration for deep learning architectures from neural responses in the human brain, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of multiple linear or nonlinear operations in creating deep learning architectures also aligns with the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an optimal approach for deep convolutional architecture, which involves natural language processing techniques, aligning with the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
